South Korea Stocks: Asiana Airlines, Kia Motors, Samsung Fire

-- B y   S a e r o m i   S h i n
-- 
2011-07-28T00:38:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/south-korea-stocks-asiana-airlines-kia-motors-samsung-fire.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in  South Korea  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 9:26 a.m. in  Seoul . The  Kospi
Index (KOSPI)  fell 23.08 points, or 1.1 percent, to 2,151.23.  Insurers: Samsung Fire & Marine Insurance Co. (000810 KS)
lost 1.9 percent to 231,500 won, heading for the lowest close
since June 17. Dongbu Insurance Co. (005830 KS) decreased 2.4
percent to 53,700 won. The companies fell after torrential rain
across South Korea caused flooding and landslides.  Asiana Airlines (020560)  Inc. (020560 KS), South Korea’s second-
largest carrier, lost 3.9 percent to 11,150 won, the most since
March 14. An Asiana cargo plane crashed in the waters off Jeju
island, the Ministry of Land, Transport and Maritime Affairs
said in a statement.  Kia Motors Corp. (000270)  (000270 KS), South Korea’s second-biggest
automaker, lost 1.6 percent to 78,100 won. Kia’s South Korean
workers rejected a tentative accord between the company and
their labor union, raising the chances of a strike. Only 47
percent of votes were cast in favor of the agreement made on
July 22, said Kim Yeon Hong, secretary general of the Korea
Metal Workers Union, an umbrella labor group for Kia employees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Saeromi Shin in Seoul at 
